						<div class="vers-content">Weep they and wail, the tipplers that must be ever at their cups, for the sweet wine they drank, and shall drink no more!<span class="content-paragraph"><br><br></span></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers169922" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">6</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Alas, my country, how valiant an enemy is this, in number past all counting, that comes to invade thee; lion nor lionâ€™s whelp has teeth can grind so pitilessly.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers169923" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">7</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Spoiled thy vineyards lie, stripped of the very bark thy fig-trees; bare and blanched and ruinous every bough.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers169924" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">8</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Weep bitterly, then, as maid that goes clad in sackcloth, untimely widowed;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers169925" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">9</div>
						<div class="vers-content">in the Lordâ€™s house, bread nor wine is offered now; for the priests, the Lordâ€™s own ministers, no office now but tears.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers169926" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">10</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Desolate the land lies, every field forlorn; crops ravaged, the vine thirsty, strengthless the oil.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers169927" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">11</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Alas, for husbandmanâ€™s labour lost, for vintage-song turned to lament! Alas for harvest perished,</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers169928" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">12</div>
						<div class="vers-content">for vineyard withered, and drooping fig-tree! Pomegranate, and palm, and apple, no tree in the wood but fades there; what wonder? Has not joy faded in human hearts?<span class="content-paragraph"><br><br></span></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers169929" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">13</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Mourn, priests, and lament; in mournersâ€™ garb go about your work at the altar; ministers of God, to his presence betake you, and there, in sackcloth, keep vigil; your Godâ€™s house, that offering of bread and wine has none!</div>
					</div>
